<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="32">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="32">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Pilidiophora" family="Lineidae" genus="Acari" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acari kesiyae" order="Heteronemertea" pageId="13" pageNumber="32" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="kesiyae">kesiyae</taxonomicName>
refers to the tree host of all beetles and mites from which the 12 isolates of this species were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
